 :tx/rationale "ASSESSMENT RISK: Formalism Cost May Exceed Value — Risk 5. The project carries enormous formal overhead: 22 spec files, 83+ invariants with falsification conditions, 30+ ADR categories, 265 verification tasks, hypothesis ledger with 273 predictions, bilateral scans, fitness function with 7 weighted components, 8-type divergence taxonomy, 3 learning loops, trilateral coherence model, policy manifest. Each element is internally consistent and well-motivated from first principles. But the aggregate cost of maintaining this formalism — writing specs, verifying invariants, recording hypotheses, measuring F(S), running bilateral scans — may exceed the value it produces. Especially if the primary user is a single developer working with AI agents. Evidence: Sessions 036 and 028 spent significant time on administrative convergence (closing 136 tasks, 28 EPICs) rather than implementation. Issue management overhead competes with productive work. The formalism is designed to scale with team size and domain complexity — but for a solo effort, lighter-weight approaches (simple README-based tracking, git-based history) might produce comparable outcomes with less ceremony. MITIGATION: This is not a risk to eliminate but to monitor. The saw-tooth model is the diagnostic: if F(S) moves after the verification sprint, the formalism is earning its keep — the measurement apparatus is detecting real convergence. If F(S) doesn't move, the formalism may be measuring itself rather than reality. S0-CLOSE validation is the ultimate test: does all this formal machinery produce better outcomes than a simpler approach on external projects? VERIFICATION: Compare braid-managed external project outcomes to baseline (no braid, just git + notes). If braid scores significantly higher → formalism justified. If comparable → formalism overhead not earning its cost. INTERACTS WITH: S0-CLOSE proposal (ultimate value test), complexity acceleration risk (formalism is a contributor to LOC growth), scope creep (spec writing creates its own backlog). TRACES TO: ADR-FOUNDATION-014, C5 (traceability), C6 (falsifiability)."
